
Endeavour OS Legacy install
Used on Lenovo Thinkcentre M81
Flash drive I create on Windows 8.1 with rufus formatted as MBR
(on Linux with dd command do not boot)

Grub loader, because there is no boot loader

12 mb unformated
17 gb swap swap
42 gb root
50 gb home


--------------------------------------------
This is UEFI installation it not work on M81
Flash drive can be created on linux with dd command

Endeavour OS UEFI
512MB fat32 /boot/efi - bios-grub, boot
35-42GB ext4 / - root
50GB ext4 /home

--------------------------------------------
Used April.2024 on Lenovo Thinkcentre M81
1. GPT Table - it is good to use GPT because it allow more than 4 primary partitions
2. Unformated 9 mb with bios-grub flag
3. Create partition 35 GB and map it for / (root)
4. Home partition 50-70 GB and map it for /home
5. linuxswap 16 GB for Computer with 16 GB RAM flag swap

